quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,43,"And We did not send before you except men, towards whom We sent divine revelations – so O people, ask the people of knowledge if you do not know. (* All the Prophets were men.)"
  16,44,"Along with clear proofs and writings; and We have sent down this Remembrance towards you (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him) so that you may explain to mankind what has been revealed towards them, and that they may ponder."
  16,45,"So do they who conspire evils, not fear that Allah may bury them in the earth, or that the punishment may come to them from a place they do not know?"
  16,46,"Or that He may seize them while they move here and there, for they cannot escape?"
  16,47,"Or that He may seize them whilst constantly ruining them? For indeed your Lord is Most Compassionate, Most Merciful."
  16,48,"And have they not observed that the shadows of the things Allah has created incline to the right and to the left, in prostration to Allah, and that they are servile?"
  16,49,"And to Allah only prostrates whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever moves in the earth, and the angels – and they are not proud."
  16,50,"They bear upon themselves the fear of their Lord, and do only what they are commanded."
  16,51,"And Allah has proclaimed, “Do not ascribe two Gods; indeed He is the only One God; therefore fear Me alone.”"
  16,52,"And to Him only belongs all whatever is in the heavens and in the earth, and obeying Him only is obligatory; so will you fear anyone other than Allah?"
  16,53,"And whatever blessings you have, are all from Allah – then whenever misfortune reaches you, towards Him only do you seek refuge."
  16,54,"And then, when He averts the misfortune from you, a group among you starts ascribing partners to their Lord!"
